.. _changelog:

####################
rnbgrader change log
####################

`Matthew Brett` (MB) wrote the code.

********
Releases
********

* 0.3.5 (Thursday May 29 2025):

  Maintenance release.

  * Move from setup.cfg to pyproject.toml build configuration.

* 0.3.4 (Wednesday October 23 2024):

  Bug fix release.

  * Update versioneer for Python 3.12.
  * Update for recent Python (iteritems -> items).
  * Filter out HTML outputs.
  * Allow arguments to passed through write_skipped

* 0.3.3 (Monday October 17 2023)

  Bug fix release.

  * Fix tests
  * Add --show-errors flag to allow raise.

* 0.3.2 (Saturday December 22 2022)

  Bug fix release.

  * Restore check for ``comm_`` messages

* 0.3.1 (Saturday December 22 2022)

  Release pulled from PyPI, see above.

  * rnbg-allow-raises accepts multiple notebooks on command line.

* 0.3 (Thursday December 22 2022)

  * Adapt to jupyter-client>=7
  * Add allow_raises code and CLI
  * Rename executable to prefix rnbg- (with deprecation warning)

* 0.2 (Monday March 30 2020)

  * Generalize to Python notebooks in RMarkdown format (courtesy of Jupytext).
  * Require Python >= 3.6
  * Remove 'clear' method from notebook kernel wrapper (doesn't easily apply
    to Python).
  * Add pre_run, post_run methods to NBRunner.
  * Add rnbgrader-exe-check script.
  * Add grader module.

* 0.1.1 (Wednesday November 14 2018)

  Add pip requirements.

* 0.1 (Wednesday November 14 2018)

  First public release
